spec.label: AI Generate Dataset
spec.description: Generate realistic dataset using OpenAI based on natural language description

params.name: template
params.label: Template (optional)
params.description: Select a predefined template or use custom

params.name: n_rows
params.label: Number of Rows
params.description: Number of rows to generate

params.name: columns
params.label: Column Names
params.description: Comma-separated column names (e.g., 'cilindrata,consumo,potenza')

params.name: description
params.label: Dataset Description
params.description: Describe in natural language what the dataset should represent and the relationships between columns

params.name: seed
params.label: Random Seed
params.description: Seed for reproducibility

params.name: dataset_name
params.label: Dataset Name (optional)
params.description: Custom name for saved dataset (auto-generated if empty)

params.name: force_regenerate
params.label: Force Regenerate
params.description: Force regeneration even if cached (costs API credits)
crea un dataset di crescita cellulare nel tempo, che tenga in consiuderazione che la curva di crescita tenderà ad un plateau

spec.label: 2D Scatter Plot
spec.description: Create interactive 2D scatter plot with color and size mapping

spec.label: K-Means Clustering
spec.description: K-Means clustering with elbow method and silhouette analysis

params.name: feature_columns
params.label: Feature Columns
params.description: Columns to use for clustering

params.name: n_clusters
params.label: Number of Clusters (K)
params.description: Number of clusters to create

params.name: auto_k
params.label: Auto-detect K
params.description: Automatically find optimal K using elbow method

params.name: max_k_search
params.label: Max K for Auto-search
params.description: Maximum K to test when auto-detecting

params.name: normalize
params.label: Normalize Features
params.description: Standardize features before clustering

params.name: plot_x
params.label: Plot X-axis
params.description: Column for X-axis in scatter plot (optional, uses first features if empty)

params.name: plot_y
params.label: Plot Y-axis
params.description: Column for Y-axis in scatter plot

params.name: plot_z
params.label: Plot Z-axis (3D)
params.description: Column for Z-axis to create 3D plot (optional)

spec.label: Regression
spec.description: Train regression models (Linear, Ridge, Lasso, RF, GBM, SVR)

spec.label: Train/Test Split
spec.description: Split dataset into training and testing sets

params.name: stratify_column
params.label: Stratify by Column (optional)
params.description: Column name for stratified split

params.name: value

params.description: Numeric value to output

params.name: label
params.label: Label
params.description: Optional label for this value

spec.label: Custom Table
spec.description: Create table data visually - click 'Edit Table' to start. Numeric inputs are written to the first available columns (Input 1 → Column 1, Input 2 → Column 2, etc.). Each execution adds a new row.

params.name: table_data
params.label: Table Data (Internal)
params.description: Internal storage for table data

params.name: reset_on_execute
params.label: Reset on Execute
params.description: Clear accumulated data when workflow is executed

params.description: Last row to include (exclusive, like Python slicing)

params.name: step
params.label: Step
params.description: Take every Nth row (1 = all rows)
